::: RC8 Update! :::

:::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
::: Silent_mode.bat by John Paul Edwards April 10, 2023
:::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
::: Launch AAA_Sync in Silent Mode, output to Logfile :::
:::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
:::     -- output to Logfile Pending: rev 8.2+ --
:::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::

             :::::::[ PROGRAM MAIN ]:::::::
  @echo off
  if not defined vers set vers=v8.5.7.81 20230720013918 by -JpE-

:main
  set titl2=Silent_mode.bat %vers% launched: %date% @ %time%
  title %titl2%
  set bats=C:\Users\%username%\Documents\AAA Sync2Laptop\Batch Files\BCS-Suite
  if not exist "%bats%" echo . & echo Folder not found! & echo . & pause & exit
  set util1="%bats%\utility1.bat"
  if not exist %util1% echo . & echo %util1% not found! & echo . & pause & exit

::start
  set ty1=25 & set /a code2=0
  call %util1% "shotcaller"
  ::: Defaults to this ^ label if no arg passed.

REM ::: *** Test Code for ErrorHandling.bat
REM set /a code2=7

  if %code2% equ 7 goto err1
  set msg="Ready to Run Backups? (Y/n): "
  choice /c yn /n /t 10 /d y /m %msg%
  if %errorlevel% equ 2 goto return

REM ::: *** Test Code Until Ready to Rock-On!
REM echo . & echo Test Completed. & echo . & pause & echo .
REM goto return

  echo . & echo Proceeding... & echo .
  set AAA="%bats%\AAA-Sync.bat"
  if not exist %AAA% echo . & echo %AAA% not found! & echo . & goto err1
  set filename1="%bats%\overrider3.txt"
  ::: Purely a runtime file ^ see usages implementing override1 in %AAA% @:restart and the override1 var thereafter in several of the BCS code files. (Load Session, Use Search ALL Open Documents)
  if exist %filename1% del /f /s /q %filename1%
  copy %util1% %filename1% & call %AAA%
  if exist %filename1% del /f /s /q %filename1%
  title %titl2%


:return
  echo . & echo .
  set msg="Review what happened? (y/N): "
  choice /c yn /n /t %ty1% /d n /m %msg%
  if %errorlevel% equ 1 echo . & pause & echo . & goto return
  exit /b %errorlevel%
 
 
                    :::::::[ Error and Exit Routines ]:::::::
:err1
  echo oopsie an error sent Flow here. Get on it!
  set txt= OMG It fn Werked! Error Detected Successfully!
  title %txt%
  
REM ::: Testcode -
REM echo . & echo txt == %txt% & echo . & pause & echo .

  set "sender1=Silent_mode.bat"
  set err2="%bats%\ErrorHandling.bat"
  if exist %err2% call %err2% "%txt%", %sender1%
  goto return



:::  100%  -JpE-

title: ErrorHandling.bat
content:
:::  RC8 Update!  :::

:::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
:: ErrorHandling.bat by -JpE- 20220628231816 ::
:::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::

  if not defined vers set vers=v8.5.7.82 20230720014017 by -JpE-
  ::: set testwell=3 to enter test mode.
  set /a testwell=1

::: Proof of Concept for makeline function below.
:welcome
  set /a counter213=0
  set txt2= Welcome to ErrorHandling! 
  call :makeline "%txt2%" line
  echo . & echo . & echo %line%
  echo %txt2% & echo %line% & echo .
  goto start


:makeline <string strToPadTo, string line2Fill>
  if not exist %util1% echo . & echo %util1% not found! & echo . & pause & goto return
  setlocal
  set txt3=%~1
  set "newline=%~2"
  set charsForPadding=*-=-
  set sizer="%bats%\string_length.bat"
  if exist %sizer% call %sizer% chars1 charsForPadding
  set call411=caller2
  call %util1% %call411% "%txt3%" 0
  set /a size2=((%actualSize2%+%chars1%)/%chars1%)
  set call411=padder
  call %util1% %call411% "test5" %size2%
  set newline=%line1%
  endlocal & set "%~2=%newline%"  
  exit /b %errorlevel%


:start
  set txt=Backup & if not defined r3v3rs3 set /a r3v3rs3=1
  if %r3v3rs3% equ 2 set txt=RESTORE
  echo . & set myLine1= Calling the ErrorHandling.bat  %vers% 
  call :makeline "%myLine1%" line
  set /a larger1=%actualSize2% & set line4=%line%  
  set myLine2= ATTENTION: AN ERROR HAS JUST OCCURRED IN THE %oper% %txt% Operation. & call :makeline "%myLine2%" line
  if %actualSize2% gtr %larger1% set line4=%line%
  echo %line4% & echo %myLine1%
  echo %line4% & echo %myLine2% & echo %line4% & echo .
  if not defined where set /a where=0
  if %where% gtr 5 goto fatal
  if %code2% equ 5 (goto nothingSent) else (if %code2% neq 7 if exist %test% goto unhandled)
  ::: SPLIT DOWN TO ISOLATE NEWEST CODE BELOW.
  if %testwell% equ 3 call :testcode
  goto tester


:drive
  echo %l2% & echo . & echo " >>===> UNLOCK BITLOCKER for D:\ AND TRY AGAIN." & echo .
  set msg="Are you ready to try again? (Y/n): "
  choice /c yn /n /t 180 /d y /m %msg%
  echo . & echo %l2% & if %errorlevel% neq 2 set /a exit2=5
  if %counter213% lss 3 set /a counter213+=1 & goto drive
  goto return


:okay
  echo .
  echo %sl%
  echo          ****  Operation  (s) Cancelled by: %username%  ****
  echo %sl%
  echo .
  echo %line%
  goto return


::: Fatal Error! ** if %where% equ 6 **
:fatal
  echo %l2% & echo . & echo %sl%
  echo            **  "FATAL ERROR: #"%where% <-===<< **
  echo           **** "copies_backups.bat" Can't be Found! ****
  echo %sl% & echo . & pause & echo . & echo %l2% & set /a exit2=6
  goto return


:::  DEVELOPING (as needed below)
:::  echo if %where% equ 1 thru 4 then blah blah bla
:::  Called from copy_control.bat
:unhandled
  echo %time%
  call :testcode
  echo An unhandled exception has occurred
  echo in the copy-subs some "where:"
  echo . & echo where == %where% & echo . & pause & echo .
  goto return


  :::-=[ DANGER! UNDER CONSTRUCTION. HARD HAT REQUIRED ]=-:::

:testcode <GLOBAL: no args sent or returned>
  echo errorlevel == %errorlevel% & echo . & echo code2 == %code2% & echo . & pause & echo .
  exit /b %errorlevel%


::: Analyze what code2==7 really means and what we need to do about it.
:next <stringVar msg1, stringVar sender, stringVarReturned next>
echo . & echo Made it to :next! & echo . & pause & echo .
  setlocal
  set "msg1=%~1"
  set "sender=%~2"
  set "next=%~3"
  echo .
  echo .
  REM echo handles errors from other files. & if %sender% equ "Silent_mode.bat" (set next=DoThis) else (set next=DoThat)
  echo .
  echo msg1 == %msg1%, and batfile caller == %sender%
  call :testcode
  if %errorlevel% equ 0 echo . & echo The :next function succeeded! & echo . & pause & echo .
::: To TestWell
set "sender=util2.bat"
  if %sender% == "Silent_mode.bat" (set "next=next1") else (set "next=next2")
  endlocal & set "%~3=%next%"
  exit /b %errorlevel%


::: next1 experiment
:next1
  echo . & set line1= This error was detected in the Silent_mode.bat Code File.
  call :makeline %line1% line
  echo %line% & echo %line1% & echo %line% & echo . & pause & echo .
  
echo Made it to NEXT1! & echo . & pause & echo .

  goto return


:tester
  if %code2% equ 7 call :next "%~1" "%~2" num
  if %testwell% equ 3 call :testcode
  if %code2% neq 7 goto return
  
  ::: It is now implicite that errorlevel is zero and code2 == 7!
  if %errorlevel% neq 0 echo . & echo OH NO! & echo . & pause & echo . & goto return
  if %testwell% neq 3 echo . & echo NOT IN TEST MODE RIGHT NOW! & echo . & goto return

echo . & echo num == %num% & echo . & pause & echo .

  if %num% neq "" (call :%num%) else (echo echo . & echo Unanticipated! & echo . & pause & goto unhandled)
  goto return


:next2 <stringVar sender, stringVar result>
  setlocal
  set "sender=%~1"
  set "result=%~2"
  echo The error was detected in %sender% on %date% @ %time%
  set result= I'm not sure what this will eventually do.

echo . & echo Now we have hit "next2" function! & echo . & echo sender == %sender%, and result == %result% & echo . & pause & echo .

  endlocal & set "%~2=%result%"
  exit /b %errorlevel%

::: Early Design Phase Only, down in here. Experimenting.

:nothingSent
  echo . & echo Nothing THERE-ERROR! & echo . & pause & echo .


  goto return

REM ::: ^ UNDER CONSTRUCTION (Layout)


:return
REM :: TESTCODE
REM echo . & echo The End of ErrorHandling module. & echo . & pause & echo .
  exit /b %errorlevel%



:: 100% -JpE-

title: runtime_display.bat
content:
::: RC8 Update! :::

:::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
::: Split out from SyncOlderPhotos.bat Sept 8th, 2022   :::
::: For reUsages with other things. see set vars below. :::
::: set vers=v7.9.7.64 20221104054808 by -JpE-          :::
:::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
:::   Runtime Display Module Copyright 2023 by -JpE-    :::
:::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::

::: <These vars must be set:>
::: set timethen=%time%
::: set datethen=%date%
::: <ASSURE ^ THESE ARE SET IN START OF ALL CALLERS!>

  set /a test21=(1)
  ::: Set test21 ^ to 7 for trace mode, else it's off.
  if not defined vers set vers=v8.5.7.81 20230720013918 by -JpE-

:runtime
  echo    %sl%
  echo                  Runtime Display Ultra Pro Deluxe 8
  echo    %sl%
  echo                 %vers%
  echo    %sl%
  echo .
  echo **%l1%**
  set calcdate=%date%
  set calctime=%time%

  ::: =====================[ NOW BEGIN ]=====================
  set yearnow=%date:~0,4%
  set /a yrn=(%yearnow%)
  :::
  set montnow=%date:~5,2%
  if "%montnow:~0,1%" equ " " set montnow=%montnow:~1,1%
  if "%montnow:~0,1%" equ "0" set montnow=%montnow:~1,1%
  set /a mtn=(%montnow%)
  :::
  set daysnow=%date:~8,2%
  if "%daysnow:~0,1%" equ " " set daysnow=%daysnow:~1,1%
  if "%daysnow:~0,1%" equ "0" set daysnow=%daysnow:~1,1%
  set /a dyn=(%daysnow%)  
  if %test21% == 7 echo . & echo pause-1 & echo . & pause & echo .


  :::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
  ::: Hours | Minutes | Seconds :::
  :::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::  
  set hournow=%time:~0,2%
  if "%hournow:~0,1%" equ " " set hournow=%hournow:~1,1%
  if "%hournow:~0,1%" equ "0" set hournow=%hournow:~1,1%
  set /a hrn=(%hournow%)
  :::
  if %test21% == 7 echo . & echo pause-2 & echo . & pause & echo .
  set minsnow=%time:~3,2%
  if "%minsnow:~0,1%" equ " " set minsnow=%minsnow:~1,1%
  if "%minsnow:~0,1%" equ "0" set minsnow=%minsnow:~1,1%
  set /a min=(%minsnow%)
  :::
  if %test21% == 7 echo . & echo pause-2a & echo . & pause & echo .
  set secsnow=%time:~6,2%
  if "%secsnow:~0,1%" equ " " set secsnow=%secsnow:~1,1%
  if "%secsnow:~0,1%" equ "0" set secsnow=%secsnow:~1,1%
  set /a scn=(%secsnow%)
  :::
  if %test21% == 7 echo . & echo pause-2b & echo . & pause & echo .
  set centinow=%time:~9,2%
  if "%centinow:~0,1%" equ " " set centinow=%centinow:~1,1%
  if "%centinow:~0,1%" equ "0" set centinow=%centinow:~1,1%
  set /a mln=(%centinow%)
  if %test21% == 7 echo . & echo pause-3 & echo . & pause & echo .


  ::: =====================[ NOW END ]=====================
  :::       SUPER-PARSER DELUXE : PARSING EXAMPLE
  ::: =====================================================

  ::::::::::::::::::::::::[ THEN BEGIN ]:::::::::::::::::::::
  set yearthen=%datethen:~0,4%
  set /a yrt=(%yearthen%)
  :::
  set montthen=%datethen:~5,2%
  if "%montthen:~0,1%" equ " " set montthen=%montthen:~1,1%
  if "%montthen:~0,1%" equ "0" set montthen=%montthen:~1,1%
  set /a mtt=(%montthen%)
  if %test21% == 7 echo . & echo pause-4 & echo . & pause & echo .
  :::
  set daysthen=%datethen:~8,2%
  if "%daysthen:~0,1%" equ " " set daysthen=%daysthen:~1,1%
  if "%daysthen:~0,1%" equ "0" set daysthen=%daysthen:~1,1%
  set /a dyt=(%daysthen%)
  if %test21% == 7 echo . & echo pause-4a & echo . & pause & echo .
  :::
  set hourthen=%timethen:~0,2%
  if "%hourthen:~0,1%" equ " " set hourthen=%hourthen:~1,1%
  if "%hourthen:~0,1%" equ "0" set hourthen=%hourthen:~1,1%
  set /a hrt=(%hourthen%)  
  if %test21% == 7 echo . & echo pause-5 & echo . & pause & echo .
  :::
  set minsthen=%timethen:~3,2%
  if "%minsthen:~0,1%" equ " " set minsthen=%minsthen:~1,1%
  if "%minsthen:~0,1%" equ "0" set minsthen=%minsthen:~1,1%
  set /a mit=(%minsthen%)
  :::
  set secsthen=%timethen:~6,2%
  if "%secsthen:~0,1%" equ " " set secsthen=%secsthen:~1,1%
  if "%secsthen:~0,1%" equ "0" set secsthen=%secsthen:~1,1%
  set /a sct=(%secsthen%)
  :::
  set centithen=%timethen:~9,2%
  if "%centithen:~0,1%" equ " " set centithen=%centithen:~1,1%
  if "%centithen:~0,1%" equ "0" set centithen=%centithen:~1,1%
  set /a mlt=(%centithen%)
  ::::::::::::::::::::::::[ THEN END ]:::::::::::::::::::::


  ::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
  ::: Days In Month aka dim, I know right. :::
  ::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
  set /a day=365
  set /a "mod=%yrn% %% 4%"
  if %mod% equ 0 set /a day=366
  set /a dim=31
  if %mtn% neq 2 goto notfeb

  ::: February regular or Leap Year!
  set /a dim=28
  if %mod% equ 0 set /a dim=29

:notfeb
  ::: 30 days hath September, April, June, && November!!!
  ::: (all the rest have 31, except for february which
  ::: has 28, unless the year / 4 == whole-number,
  ::: in which case it's leap year & Feb has 29 days! (above) -ed
  if %mtn% equ 9 set /a dim=30 
  if %mtn% equ 4 set /a dim=30
  if %mtn% equ 6 set /a dim=30 
  if %mtn% equ 11 set /a dim=30

  :::::::::::::::::::::
  ::: Month as Word :::
  :::::::::::::::::::::
  set mt=January
  if %mtn% equ 2 set mt=February
  if %mtn% equ 3 set mt=March
  if %mtn% equ 4 set mt=April
  if %mtn% equ 5 set mt=May
  if %mtn% equ 6 set mt=June
  if %mtn% equ 7 set mt=July
  if %mtn% equ 8 set mt=August
  if %mtn% equ 9 set mt=September
  if %mtn% equ 10 set mt=October
  if %mtn% equ 11 set mt=November
  if %mtn% equ 12 set mt=December


  :::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
  ::: Day of Week as a Word:  :::
  :::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
  set util2="%bats%\utility2.bat"
  if exist %util2% call %util2% dayOfWeek
  ::: Mod 20230718030330 v8.5.6.77 :::
  ::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
  if %test21% == 7 echo . & echo pause-6 & echo . & pause & echo .


  ::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
  ::: Partial Duplicate to Screen. :::
  ::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
  set ext=th
  set ned=th
  if %dyn% == 1 set ned=st
  if %dyn% == 21 set ned=st
  if %dyn% == 31 set ned=st
  if %mtn% == 1 set ext=st
  if %dyn% == 2 set ned=nd
  if %dyn% == 22 set ned=nd
  if %mtn% == 2 set ext=nd
  if %dyn% == 3 set ned=rd
  if %dyn% == 23 set ned=rd
  if %mtn% == 3 set ext=rd
  if %mod% == 0 set msg=IT'S LEAPYEAR!

  if %test21% == 7 echo . & echo pause-7 & echo . & pause & echo .

  ::: !!! R3 mods !!!
  set mlclc=%calctime:~9,2%
  if "%mlclc:~0,1%" equ " " set mlclc=%mlclc:~1,1%
  if "%mlclc:~0,1%" equ "0" set mlclc=%mlclc:~1,1%
  set /a mlclc=(%mlclc%)
  set nowtime=%time%
  :::  ^ for syncronization precision below.

  ::: strings to numbers...
  set mlnow=%nowtime:~9,2%
  if "%mlnow:~0,1%" equ " " set mlnow=%mlnow:~1,1%
  if "%mlnow:~0,1%" equ "0" set mlnow=%mlnow:~1,1%
  set /a mlnow=(%mlnow%)

  ::: Now Do the numerical calculations...
  set /a rtp=(%mlnow%-%mlclc%)
  if %rtp% lss 0 set /a rtp+=100
  ::: add -num is subtraction ^

  ::: Then our new numbers go back to padded strings!
  set rtpt=%rtp%
  if %rtp% leq 9 set "rtpt=0%rtpt%"

  ::: To display.
  echo **%sl%         **
  echo **%l1%**
  
  ::: !!! revised RC8-v8.5.6.80 mods CONDENSED - REUSABLE !!!
  set strlen="%bats%\string_length.bat"
  set pads="%bats%\add_padding.bat"
  ::: vvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvvv
  set line=It's %dayOfWeek% %mt% %daysnow%%ned%, %yearnow% @ %nowtime%
  if exist %pads% if exist %strlen% call %pads%
  echo **      %line%**
  if %test21% == 7 echo . & echo pause-8 & echo . & pause & echo .
  ::: ^v extended uses of set line=bla & call %pads%
  set line=Processing Time was: 0.%rtpt% seconds on this System!
  if exist %pads% if exist %strlen% call %pads%
  echo **      %line%**
  echo **%l1%**
  if %test21% == 7 echo . & echo pause-9 & echo . & pause & echo .
  ::: 
  set line=Program Started: %datethen% @ %timethen%
  if exist %pads% if exist %strlen% call %pads%
  echo **      %line%**
  ::: 
  set line=Program Finish:  %calcdate% @ %calctime%
  if exist %pads% if exist %strlen% call %pads%
  echo **      %line%**
  echo **%l1%**
  ::: 
  set line=%mt% is the %mtn%%ext% month. %mt% has %dim% days.
  if exist %pads% if exist %strlen% call %pads%
  echo **      %line%**
  ::: 
  if %mod% equ 0 set line=%msg% & if exist %pads% if exist %strlen% call %pads% &  echo **%l1%** & echo **      %line%**
  if %test21% == 7 echo . & echo pause-10 & echo . & pause & echo .
  ::: end R8 mods


  :::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
  :: Calculate how long it has been. ::
  :::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
  set /a centi=(%mln%-%mlt%)
  if %centi% lss 0 set /a scn-=1 & set /a "centi=(100+%centi%)"

  set /a secs=(%scn%-%sct%)
  if %secs% lss 0 set /a min-=1 & set /a "secs=(60+%secs%)"

  set /a mins=(%min%-%mit%)
  if %mins% lss 0 set /a hrn-=1 & set /a "mins=(60+%mins%)"

  set /a hour=(%hrn%-%hrt%)
  if %hour% lss 0 set /a dyn-=1 & set /a "hour=(24+%hour%)"

  set /a days=(%dyn%-%dyt%)
  if %days% lss 0 set /a mtn-=1 & set /a "days=(%dim%+%days%)"

  set /a mnth=(%mtn%-%mtt%)
  if %mnth% lss 0 set /a yrn-=1 & set /a "mnth=(12+%mnth%)"

  set /a year=(%yrn%-%yrt%)
  if %year% lss 0 set /a "year=0"

  if %test21% == 7 echo . & echo pause-11 & echo . & pause & echo .


  ::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
  :: Check all values and Pad text
  ::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
  if %year% lss 0 goto err

  set yrs=%year%
  if %year% lss 10 set yrs=0%year%
  ::
  if %mnth% lss 0 goto err
  if %mnth% gtr 12 goto err

  if %test21% == 7 echo . & echo pause-12 & echo . & pause & echo .

  set mts=%mnth%
  if %mnth% lss 10 set mts=0%mnth%
  ::
  if %days% lss 0 goto err
  if %days% gtr %dim% goto err

  set dys=%days%
  if %days% lss 10 set dys=0%days%
  ::
  if %hour% lss 0 goto err
  if %hour% gtr 23 goto err

  set hrs=%hour%
  if %hour% lss 10 set hrs=0%hour%
  ::
  if %mins% lss 0 goto err
  if %mins% gtr 59 goto err

  if %test21% == 7 echo . & echo pause-13 & echo . & pause & echo .

  set mns=%mins%
  if %mins% lss 10 set mns=0%mins%
  ::
  if %secs% lss 0 goto err
  if %secs% gtr 59 goto err

  set scs=%secs%
  if %secs% lss 10 set scs=0%secs%
  ::
  if %centi% lss 0 goto err
  if %centi% gtr 99 goto err

  set mli=%centi%
  if %centi% lss 10 set mli=0%centi%

  if %test21% == 7 echo . & echo pause-14 & echo . & pause & echo .

  ::::::::::::::::::::
  :: Log Code 7     ::
  ::::::::::::::::::::
  :: RESULTS CHECK  ::
  ::::::::::::::::::::
  echo **%l1%**
  set line=Runtime Calculated with RunT-8.5.6
  if exist %pads% if exist %strlen% call %pads%
  echo **      %line%**
  set line= ==================================
  if exist %pads% if exist %strlen% call %pads%
  echo **     %line% **
  set line=%yrs% years, %mts% months,  %dys% days,
  if exist %pads% if exist %strlen% call %pads%
  echo **      %line%**
  set line=%hrs% hours, %mns% minutes, %scs%.%mli% seconds.
  if exist %pads% if exist %strlen% call %pads%
  echo **      %line%**
  echo **%l1%**
  set line=Bye Bye For Now! Fare Well. Come Again. Adios!
  if exist %pads% if exist %strlen% call %pads%
  echo **      %line%**
  echo **%l1%**
  echo .
  goto return

:err
  echo **%l2%**
  set line=Error Detected, Please Review it.
  if exist %pads% if exist %strlen% call %pads%
  echo **      %line%**
  echo **%l2%**
  :: Programmatic pause for beta test user action.
  pause
  echo %l2%

:return
  if %test21% == 7 echo Pause-END & pause

content:
#My Samba Share with Public+Private Share (Ubuntu)
 
su
apt-get install samba
 
cat > /etc/samba/smb.conf << SMBCONF
 [global]
 server min protocol = SMB2_02
 server max protocol = SMB3
 server string = fileserver
 workgroup = WORKGROUP
 netbios name = fileserver
 wins support = yes
 local master = yes
 preferred master = yes
 time server = yes
 security = auto
 unix extensions = yes
 name resolve order = lmhosts host wins bcast
 include = /etc/samba/shares.conf
SMBCONF

cat > /etc/samba/shares.conf << SHARECONF
  [Public]
 path = /fileserver/files/public_files
 force group = smbgroup
 create mask = 0750
 force create mode = 0750
 directory mask = 0750
 force directory mode = 0750
 public = yes
 writable = yes
 hide unreadable = Yes
 access based share enum = Yes
 nt acl support = yes
 inherit acls = no
 SHARECONF


useradd -s /bin/false smbadmin
smbpasswd -a smbadmin
groupadd smbgroup
 
useradd -s /bin/false user1
smbpasswd -a user1
 


mkdir -p /storage/share/samba/public_files/all
mkdir -p /storage/share/samba/public_files/exchange
mkdir -p /storage/share/samba/public_files/privat/

chown smbadmin:smbgroup /storage/share/samba/public_files
chown smbadmin:smbgroup /storage/share/samba/public_files/all
chown smbadmin:smbgroup /storage/share/samba/public_files/exchange
chown smbadmin:smbgroup /storage/share/samba/public_files/privat/


chmod -R ugo-rwx /storage/share/samba/public_files/
chmod u+rwx,g+rxs,o+rx /storage/share/samba/public_files/
chmod u+rwx,g+rwxs,o+rx /storage/share/samba/public_files/all
chmod u+rwx,g+rxs,o+rx /storage/share/samba/public_files/exchange
chmod u-rwx,g-rwxs,o-rwx /storage/share/samba/public_files/privat/
chmod -R u+rwx,g+rwx-s,o-rwx /storage/share/samba/public_files/privat/*

touch /storage/share/samba/public_files/all/.lock
chmod go-rwx /storage/share/samba/public_files/all/.lock
chattr +i /storage/share/samba/public_files/all/.lock

touch /storage/share/samba/public_files/exchange/.lock
chmod go-rwx /storage/share/samba/public_files/exchange/.lock
chattr +i /storage/share/samba/public_files/exchange/.lock

touch /storage/share/samba/public_files/privat/.lock
chmod go-rwx /storage/share/samba/public_files/privat/.lock
chattr +i /storage/share/samba/public_files/privat/.lock


systemctl restart smbd

-- simple3.tb_view_report_quarterly_statuses source

CREATE OR REPLACE
ALGORITHM = UNDEFINED VIEW `simple3`.`tb_view_report_quarterly_statuses` AS
SELECT
    `t`.`data_profile_id` AS `data_profile_id`,
    json_arrayagg(json_object('quarter',
    `t`.`quarter`,
    'activity_statuses',
    `t`.`activity_statuses`)) AS `quarters`
FROM
    (
    SELECT
        `rq`.`id` AS `id`,
        `rq`.`data_profile_id` AS `data_profile_id`,
        `rqq`.`quarter` AS `quarter`,
        json_arrayagg(`rqs`.`activity`) AS `activity_statuses`
    FROM
        ((`simple3`.`report_quarterly_statuses` `rqs`
    JOIN `simple3`.`report_quarterly_quarters` `rqq` ON
        ((`rqs`.`report_quarterly_quarter_id` = `rqq`.`id`)))
    JOIN `simple3`.`report_quarterlies` `rq` ON
        ((`rq`.`id` = `rqq`.`report_quarterly_id`)))
    GROUP BY
        `rq`.`id`,
        `rqq`.`quarter`) `t`;

title: tb_view_report_quarterly
content:
-- simple3.tb_view_report_quarterly source

CREATE OR REPLACE
ALGORITHM = UNDEFINED VIEW `simple3`.`tb_view_report_quarterly` AS
SELECT
    `drdp`.`dr_id` AS `id`,
    `drdp`.`dr_id` AS `dr__id`,
    `drdp`.`dp_id` AS `dp__id`,
    `drdp`.`dr_registration_number` AS `dr__registration_number`,
    `drdp`.`dr_effective_date` AS `dr__effective_date`,
    `drdp`.`dr_closing_date` AS `dr__closing_date`,
    `c`.`name` AS `c__name`,
    `u_pic`.`name` AS `u_pic__name`,
    `u_executor`.`name` AS `u_executor__name`,
    `dps`.`total` AS `dp__disbursment_plan`,
    `dps`.`year` AS `dp__year`
FROM
    (((((((
    SELECT
        `dr`.`id` AS `dr_id`,
        `dr`.`data_mou_id` AS `dr_data_mou_id`,
        `dr`.`registration_number` AS `dr_registration_number`,
        `dr`.`effective_date` AS `dr_effective_date`,
        `dr`.`closing_date` AS `dr_closing_date`,
        `dr`.`executor` AS `dr_executor`,
        `dp`.`id` AS `dp_id`
    FROM
        (`simple3`.`data_registrations` `dr`
    JOIN `simple3`.`data_profiles` `dp` ON
        ((`dp`.`data_registration_id` = `dr`.`id`)))) `drdp`
JOIN `simple3`.`data_mous` `dm` ON
    ((`dm`.`id` = `drdp`.`dr_data_mou_id`)))
JOIN `simple3`.`contributors` `c` ON
    ((`c`.`id` = `dm`.`contributor_id`)))
JOIN `simple3`.`data_profiles` `dp` ON
    ((`dp`.`data_registration_id` = `drdp`.`dr_id`)))
JOIN `simple3`.`disbursment_plans` `dps` ON
    ((`dps`.`data_profile_id` = `dp`.`id`)))
JOIN `simple3`.`work_units` `u_pic` ON
    ((`u_pic`.`id` = `dm`.`pic`)))
JOIN `simple3`.`sub_work_units` `u_executor` ON
    ((`u_executor`.`id` = `drdp`.`dr_executor`)));

# The NUM_PUBLICATIONS_QUERY counts the number of publications in the English language.
NUM_PUBLICATIONS_QUERY = """
select
count(id) as Number_of_Publications
from
result r
where
r.type = 'publication'
and r.language = 'English'
and year(r.dateofacceptance) >= {}
and year(r.dateofacceptance) <= {}
"""

# The NUM_PUBLICATIONS_WITH_DOI_QUERY counts the number of publications in English
# language that also has DOI.
NUM_PUBLICATIONS_WITH_DOI_QUERY = """
select
count(r.id) Number_of_Publications_with_DOI
from
result as r
join
result_instance_pid as rip on r.id = rip.result
where
r.type = 'publication'
and r.language = 'English'
and year(r.dateofacceptance) >= {}
and year(r.dateofacceptance) <= {}
and rip.type == 'Digital Object Identifier'
"""

# The NUM_PUBLICATIONS_PER_NUM_DOI_QUERY counts the number of publications in English
# language that also have DOI and counts the publications with one or more DOI.
NUM_PUBLICATIONS_PER_NUM_DOI_QUERY = """
with dois as (
select
r.id,
size(collect_set(pid)) as num_doi
from
result as r
join
result_instance_pid as rip on r.id = rip.result
where
r.type = 'publication'
and r.language = 'English'
and year(r.dateofacceptance) >= {}
and year(r.dateofacceptance) <= {}
and rip.type == 'Digital Object Identifier'
group by
r.id
)
select
case num_doi
when 1 then 'Number_of_DOI=1'
else 'Number_of_DOI>1'
end as DOI_Category,
count(*) as Number_of_Publications
from
dois
where
num_doi = 1 or num_doi > 1
group by
DOI_Category
"""

# The NUM_PUBLICATIONS_AND_NUM_TITLE_QUERY counts the publications that have a) no title,
# b) exactly one title, and c) more than one title.
NUM_PUBLICATIONS_AND_NUM_TITLE_QUERY = """
with titles as (
select
r.id,
size(collect_set(t.title)) as num_titles
from
result as r
join
result_titles as t on r.id = t.id
where
r.type = 'publication'
and r.language = 'English'
and year(r.dateofacceptance) >= {}
and year(r.dateofacceptance) <= {}
group by
r.id
)
select
case num_titles
when 0 then 'Number_of_Titles=0'
when 1 then 'Number_of_Titles=1'
else 'Number_of_Titles>1'
end as Title_Category,
count(*) as Number_of_Publications
from
titles
where
num_titles = 0 or num_titles = 1 or num_titles > 1
group by
Title_Category
"""

# The NUM_PUBLICATIONS_WITH_DOI_AND_NUM_TITLE_QUERY counts the publications that have DOI
# and also have a) no title, b) exactly one title, and c) more than one titles.
NUM_PUBLICATIONS_WITH_DOI_AND_NUM_TITLE_QUERY = """
with titles as (
select
r.id,
size(collect_set(t.title)) as num_titles
from
result as r
join
result_instance_pid as rip on r.id = rip.result
join
result_titles as t on r.id = t.id
where
r.type = 'publication'
and r.language = 'English'
and year(r.dateofacceptance) >= {}
and year(r.dateofacceptance) <= {}
and rip.type == 'Digital Object Identifier'
group by
r.id
)
select
case num_titles
when 0 then 'Number_of_Titles=0'
when 1 then 'Number_of_Titles=1'
else 'Number_of_Titles>1'
end as Title_Category,
count(*) as Number_of_Publications
from
titles
where
num_titles = 0 or num_titles = 1 or num_titles > 1
group by
Title_Category
"""

# The NUM_PUBLICATIONS_AND_NUM_ABSTRACT_QUERY counts the publications that have
# a) no abstract, b) exactly one abstract, and c) more than one abstract.
NUM_PUBLICATIONS_AND_NUM_ABSTRACT_QUERY = """
with abstracts as (
select
r.id,
size(collect_set(a.description)) as num_abstracts
from
result as r
join
result_description as a on r.id = a.id
where
r.type = 'publication'
and r.language = 'English'
and year(r.dateofacceptance) >= {}
and year(r.dateofacceptance) <= {}
group by
r.id
)
select
case num_abstracts
when 0 then 'Number_of_Abstracts=0'
when 1 then 'Number_of_Abstracts=1'
else 'Number_of_Abstracts>1'
end as Abstract_Category,
count(*) as Number_of_Publications
from
abstracts
where
num_abstracts = 0 or num_abstracts = 1 or num_abstracts > 1
group by
Abstract_Category
"""

# The NUM_PUBLICATIONS_WITH_DOI_AND_NUM_ABSTRACT_QUERY counts the publications that have
# DOI and also have a) no abstract, b) exactly one abstract, and c) more than one
# abstracts.
NUM_PUBLICATIONS_WITH_DOI_AND_NUM_ABSTRACT_QUERY = """
with abstracts as (
select
r.id,
size(collect_set(a.description)) as num_abstracts
from
result as r
join
result_instance_pid as rip on r.id = rip.result
join
result_description as a on r.id = a.id
where
r.type = 'publication'
and r.language = 'English'
and year(r.dateofacceptance) >= {}
and year(r.dateofacceptance) <= {}
and rip.type == 'Digital Object Identifier'
group by
r.id
)
select
case num_abstracts
when 0 then 'Number_of_Abstracts=0'
when 1 then 'Number_of_Abstracts=1'
else 'Number_of_Abstracts>1'
end as Abstract_Category,
count(*) as Number_of_Publications
from
abstracts
where
num_abstracts = 0 or num_abstracts = 1 or num_abstracts > 1
group by
Abstract_Category
"""

title: Обучите модель в GPU-тренажёре
content:
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense, GlobalAveragePooling2D
from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential
from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing.image import ImageDataGenerator
from tensorflow.keras.applications.resnet import ResNet50
from tensorflow.keras.optimizers import Adam
from tensorflow.keras.metrics import MeanAbsoluteError
import pandas as pd

 
def load_train(path):
    data = pd.read_csv(str(path)+'labels.csv')
    train_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(rescale=1 / 255., validation_split=0.25)
    train_datagen_flow = train_datagen.flow_from_dataframe(
        dataframe=data,
        directory= str(path)+'final_files/',
        target_size=(150, 150),
        batch_size=16,
        class_mode='sparse',
        subset='training',
        seed=12345)
     
    return train_datagen_flow 

def load_test(path):
    data = pd.read_csv(str(path)+'labels.csv')
    train_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(rescale=1 / 255., validation_split=0.25)
    test_datagen_flow = train_datagen.flow_from_dataframe(
        dataframe=data,
        directory= str(path)+'final_files/',
        target_size=(150, 150),
        batch_size=16,
        class_mode='sparse',
        subset='validation',
        seed=12345)
    return test_datagen_flow
    
    
def create_model(input_shape):
    backbone = ResNet50(input_shape=(150, 150, 3),
                        weights='imagenet',
                        include_top=False)

    model = Sequential()
    model.add(backbone)
    model.add(GlobalAveragePooling2D())
    model.add(Dense(1, activation='relu'))
 
    model.compile(loss='mse', metrics=[MeanAbsoluteError()], optimizer = 'adam')
 
    return model
 
def train_model(model, train_data, test_data, batch_size=None, epochs=3,
               steps_per_epoch=None, validation_steps=None):
 
    model.fit(train_data,
              validation_data=test_data,
              batch_size=batch_size,
              epochs=epochs,
              steps_per_epoch=steps_per_epoch,
              validation_steps=validation_steps,
              verbose=2)
    return model

    />
    )}
</FormGroup>

DB Extract und Upload
content:
import requests
from requests.auth import HTTPBasicAuth
import json
import mysql.connector

# API-Endpunkt
api_url = 'https://www.domain.at/api/api.php'

# Benutzername und Passwort für die Authentifizierung
username = ''
serverpassword = ''

# Verbindung zur MySQL-Datenbank herstellen
cnx = mysql.connector.connect(
    host='localhost',
    user='',
    password='',
    database=''
)

# Cursor erstellen
cursor = cnx.cursor()

# SQL-Abfrage zum Abrufen des letzten Eintrags
query = "SELECT * FROM `hofer_tankstelle` ORDER BY Zeit DESC LIMIT 1"

# SQL-Abfrage ausführen
cursor.execute(query)

# Ergebnis abrufen
result = cursor.fetchone()

# Daten aus dem Ergebnis extrahieren
zeit = result[0]
tankstelle = result[1]
adresse = result[2]
preis = str(result[3])
treibstoff = result[4]

# Verbindung zur Datenbank schließen
cursor.close()
cnx.close()

# Daten im JSON-Format zusammenstellen
data = {
    'zeit': str(zeit),
    'tankstelle': tankstelle,
    'adresse': adresse,
    'preis': preis,
    'treibstoff': treibstoff
}

# Daten als JSON serialisieren
json_data = json.dumps(data)

# GET-Request mit Basic-Authentifizierung senden
response_auth = requests.get(api_url, auth=HTTPBasicAuth(username, serverpassword))

# Antwort des Servers verarbeiten
if response_auth.status_code == 200:
    # POST-Request an die API senden
    headers = {'Content-Type': 'application/json'}
    response = requests.post(api_url, auth=HTTPBasicAuth(username, serverpassword), headers=headers, json=json_data)
    
    #Zum testen
    #print(json_data)
    print(response)
    
    # Server-Antwort anzeigen
    print(response.text)

else:
    # Fehlerhafte Anfrage
    print('Fehler:', response_auth.status_code)

title: api
content:
<?php
// Daten von POST-Anfrage empfangen
$json_data = file_get_contents('php://input');
$data = json_decode($json_data, true);

// Zum testen ob Daten empfangen worden sind
echo $json_data;

// Überprüfen der POST-Daten
if (empty($data['zeit']) || empty($data['tankstelle']) || empty($data['adresse']) || empty($data['preis']) || empty($data['treibstoff'])) {
    die("Fehler: Fehlende POST-Daten");
} else {
    // Verbindung zur MySQL-Datenbank herstellen
    require_once 'db.php';

    // SQL-Abfrage zum Einfügen der Daten
    $sql = "INSERT INTO hofer_tankstelle (Zeit, Tankstelle, Adresse, Preis, Treibstoff) VALUES (:zeit, :tankstelle, :adresse, :preis, :treibstoff)";

    try {
        global $pdo;
        $stmt = $pdo->prepare($sql);
        $stmt->bindParam(':zeit', $data['zeit']);
        $stmt->bindParam(':tankstelle', $data['tankstelle']);
        $stmt->bindParam(':adresse', $data['adresse']);
        $stmt->bindParam(':preis', $data['preis']);
        $stmt->bindParam(':treibstoff', $data['treibstoff']);
        $stmt->execute();
        echo "Daten erfolgreich in die Datenbank eingefügt.";
    } catch (PDOException $e) {
        die("Fehler beim Einfügen der Daten: " . $e->getMessage());
    }
}
?>
